---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteNav from '../../components/SiteNav.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../../components/SiteFooter.astro';
import PageScripts from '../../components/PageScripts.astro';
import { SITE } from '../../data/site.js';
import { breadcrumbSchema } from '../../lib/seo.js';

const navLinks = [
  { label: 'NBN Plans', href: '/nbn/' },
  { label: 'Repairs', href: '/repairs/' },
  { label: 'Shop', href: '/shop/' },
  { label: 'Blog', href: '/blog/' },
];

const schema = breadcrumbSchema([
  { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
  { name: 'Business NBN', path: '/nbn/' },
  { name: 'Service Terms', path: '/nbn/terms/' },
]);
---
<Layout
  title="NBN Service Terms | Express Repairs"
  description="Terms of service for Express Repairs business NBN plans: billing, the TeleChoice customer discount, speeds, fair use, cancellation and complaints."
  path="/nbn/terms/"
  schema={schema}
  htmlAttrs={{ 'data-palette': 'electric-blue', 'data-fontpair': 'jakarta', 'data-dark': 'false' }}
>
  <SiteNav links={navLinks} ctaHref="/nbn/#enquire" />

  <main id="main-content">
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container-wide terms-wrap">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a>
          <span class="crumb-sep">/</span>
          <a href="/nbn/">Business NBN</a>
          <span class="crumb-sep">/</span>
          <span class="crumb-current">Service Terms</span>
        </nav>

        <h1 class="section-title" style="margin-top: 20px;">NBN Service Terms</h1>
        <p class="terms-updated">Effective 25 July 2026</p>

        <p>
          These terms cover the NBN internet plans sold by Mertel Pty&nbsp;Ltd (ABN 88&nbsp;644&nbsp;567&nbsp;019),
          trading as {SITE.name} ("we", "us"), of {SITE.addressShort}. By signing up for an NBN plan with us
          you agree to these terms. We've kept them in plain English on purpose.
        </p>

        <h2>1. The service</h2>
        <p>
          We sell business-grade broadband delivered over the nbn® network, supplied to us by an established
          Australian wholesale network provider. We handle your sign-up, billing and account queries; network
          faults are handled by our wholesale partner's support team, and we'll help you lodge and chase a fault
          whenever you need us to. Every plan includes unlimited data and one free static IPv4 address.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Availability and connection</h2>
        <p>
          All plans are subject to availability at your address — the nbn network technology at your premises
          (such as FTTP, FTTC or HFC) determines which speed tiers you can get. We'll confirm what's available
          before you commit to anything. Some connections need an nbn technician visit or new equipment; if
          there's any charge for that (for example, a new development fee charged by nbn co), we'll tell you the
          amount before you go ahead. Any nbn-supplied equipment remains the property of nbn co.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Speeds</h2>
        <p>
          The speeds shown on our plans are <strong>typical business-hour speeds</strong> as measured by our
          wholesale partner. Your actual speed depends on your nbn technology type, the wiring at your premises,
          your modem, Wi‑Fi conditions and network congestion. If your connection can't reach the typical speed
          of the plan you chose, tell us — we'll move you to a cheaper plan that matches what your line can do,
          or you can cancel without penalty.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Pricing and billing</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>All prices are in Australian dollars and include GST.</li>
          <li>Plans are billed monthly in advance and are month-to-month — <strong>no lock-in contracts and no exit fees</strong>.</li>
          <li>If we change a plan's price we'll give you at least 30 days' written notice. You can cancel any time before the new price takes effect.</li>
          <li>If a bill isn't paid we'll contact you before restricting or suspending the service, and we'll restore it promptly once payment is sorted.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. TeleChoice customer discount</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Customers with an active TeleChoice mobile service purchased through our store receive 10% off their NBN plan's monthly price — whether the mobile service is new or existing.</li>
          <li>The discount applies for as long as both services stay active, one discount per NBN service.</li>
          <li>If the eligible mobile service is cancelled, the NBN plan reverts to its standard price from the next billing cycle. We'll always show both prices up front.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Fair use</h2>
        <p>
          Unlimited data means we don't meter, cap or charge for usage. In return, the service must be used
          lawfully and must not be resold or used in a way that damages the network or degrades the service of
          others. If we believe use is unlawful or abusive we'll contact you before taking any action, except
          where the law requires otherwise.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Cancelling</h2>
        <p>
          You can cancel any time by calling us on {SITE.phone}, emailing, or dropping into the store. There is
          no cancellation fee. Your service stays active until the end of the billing period you've already
          paid for, and we don't charge anything beyond that.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Faults and support</h2>
        <p>
          Call us first on {SITE.phone} — if the fault is in the nbn network we'll lodge it with our wholesale
          partner and keep you posted. Plans that include an enhanced service level agreement (shown on the
          plan) receive prioritised fault restoration under our wholesale partner's eSLA terms; we'll give you
          the current eSLA response targets when you sign up.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Your consumer rights</h2>
        <p>
          Our services come with guarantees that cannot be excluded under the Australian Consumer Law. Nothing
          in these terms limits those rights, or your rights under the Telecommunications Consumer Protections
          Code.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Complaints</h2>
        <p>
          If something's wrong, tell us and we'll do our best to fix it quickly — call {SITE.phone} or visit the
          store and ask for the manager. If you're not happy with how we've handled a complaint, you can contact
          the Telecommunications Industry Ombudsman (TIO) on
          <a href="tel:1800062058">1800&nbsp;062&nbsp;058</a> or at
          <a href="https://www.tio.com.au" rel="noopener">tio.com.au</a>. The TIO is a free and independent
          dispute-resolution service.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          We collect your name, contact details and connection address to check availability, connect your
          service and bill you. That information is shared with our wholesale partner and nbn co only as needed
          to deliver the service, and is never sold. You can ask us at any time what we hold about you.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Changes to these terms</h2>
        <p>
          If we change these terms in a way that could disadvantage you, we'll give you at least 30 days'
          notice, and you can cancel without penalty before the change takes effect. The current version always
          lives at this page.
        </p>

        <p class="terms-note">
          nbn® is a registered trademark of nbn co limited. Questions about these terms? Call
          <a href={SITE.phoneHref}>{SITE.phone}</a> or visit us at {SITE.addressShort}.
        </p>

        <a href="/nbn/" class="btn btn-ghost" style="margin-top: 24px;">← Back to NBN plans</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <SiteFooter />
  <PageScripts />
</Layout>

<style>
  .terms-wrap { max-width: 760px; }
  .terms-wrap h2 { font-size: 22px; margin: 36px 0 12px; }
  .terms-wrap p, .terms-wrap li { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-muted); }
  .terms-wrap ul { padding-left: 22px; margin: 12px 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }
  .terms-wrap a { color: var(--brand-700); font-weight: 600; }
  .terms-updated { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-subtle); margin: 8px 0 28px; }
  .terms-note { margin-top: 36px; font-size: 14px; }
</style>
